      "comment": "OFF THE CHART (5) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by one length at Ballarat in a handy 24.81 beating Sharapova Star. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. In sparkling form and looks the one to beat again. ROBINSON (1) is worth forgiving for his last effort when seventh (25.53) at Ballarat over 450m. Form at the trip sound including two wins. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Worth another chance. WRECK JAMES (7) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 4 lengths at Ballarat in a handy 24.97 beating Lilly Zoom. Has a strong record from box 7, including two wins. One of the prime contenders. TALCOTT BALE (2) must be respected at his pet distance.",
